## Strict-Audit Notes (auto-generated 2026-05-07, full method-level audit)

Evidence: full source read of all `Managers/*.swift` + `AppDelegate.swift`. Task descriptions corrected to match actual implementation; only confirmed symbols are `[x]`.

**Naming corrections applied to task descriptions (actual impl differs from original spec):**
- User confirmed review/approval of `.specify/features/Swift_migration/00-DELIVERY-SUMMARY.md`, `00-MIGRATION-OVERVIEW.md`, `01-IMPLEMENTATION-GUIDE.md`, and `02-READY-TO-IMPLEMENT.md` — foundation review tasks `T1.1`–`T1.4` are marked `[x]`.
- T2B.2: `fetchVenues()` → `fetchVenuesForMovie(movieId:)` *(no generic fetchVenues)*
- T2B.9: `fetchDates(venueId:movieId:)` → `fetchDates(locationId:movieId:)` *(param renamed)*
- T2B.11: `formatDateTime(_:) -> String` → `displayText(for:ScreeningDate) -> String` *(different name)*
- T2C.2: `login(username:password:)` → `signIn(username:passwordHash:deviceId:systemVersion:)` *(renamed+extended)*
- T2C.3: `signup(user:)` → `signUp(voucher:email:username:passwordHash:deviceId:systemVersion:)` *(renamed+extended)*
- T2C.13: `fetchPurchases()` → `fetchAllPurchases()` *(renamed)*
- T2C.17: file spec was `AdminDataManager.swift` → actual file is `AdminScreeningsDataManager.swift`; class inside is `final class AdminDataManager` + `typealias AdminScreeningsDataManager = AdminDataManager` ✅ — marked `[x]`
- T2C.6: auto-injection is implemented via `APIClient` default `SessionHeaderProvider`, plus `MbooksService` / `LoginGatewayService` using `SessionHeaderProvider` / `MergedHeaderProvider` on downstream calls ✅ — marked `[x]`.
- T2A.5: `MoviesDataManager` now persists fetched movies to Realm-backed cache per movie ID (`save` replacement semantics invalidate prior entries on fetch) ✅.
- T2A.17: `reserveSeats(screeningDateId:seats:)` implemented in `SeatsDataManager` with conflict detection and local reservation state update ✅.
- T2B.3/T2B.4/T2B.5: `VenuesDataManager` now includes `getScreens(venueId:)`, `getSeatsForScreen(screenId:date:)`, plus Realm-backed per-venue cache with in-memory fast-path caches ✅.
- T2B.16: `LocationsDataManager` now includes `getCoordinates(location:)` and `getCoordinates(locationId:)` helpers ✅.
- T2C.4: `AuthDataManager.refreshToken()` implemented with persisted-session reload and authenticated validation call ✅.
- T2C.5: secure token persistence integrated via `SecureStore` (Keychain-backed) in auth/session paths; `SessionHeaderProvider` now reads secure token first ✅.
- T2C.7: `APIClient` now maps both 401 and 403 to `AppError.authRequired` ✅.
- T2C.14: `CheckoutDataManager` now interprets payment/Braintree-style failures into user-friendly messages ✅.
- T2C.18/T2C.19: `AdminDataManager` now includes `updateMovie(movie:)` and `updateVenue(venue:)`, reusing backend `admin/updatescreen` with current admin-screen context ✅.
- T2C.21: role-check guard (`AppError.forbidden`) is intentionally deferred/out of scope for this migration pass.
- T3.7: unused `MoviesVC` instance vars (`data`, `venueData`) removed and replaced with local row vars ✅.
- T4.3: auth error handling present across `LoginVC`/`SignupVC`/`MenuVC` with `ErrorHandler.message(for:)` + user alerts ✅.

**Open gaps (tasks remain `[ ]`):**
- T1.8: warning-free compile for protocol scope not separately evidenced in this audit pass
- **Phase 3+ VC migration tasks:** MoviesVC, VenuesVC, `iOSCalenderVC.swift`, and SeatsVC (`PopOver.swift`) confirmed migrated. Repo-wide sweep across top-level `SwiftLoginScreen/*.swift` UI files found **0** remaining direct `services.mbooks` / `app.services` / `AppDelegate.services` calls. `BasketData.swift` uses `screeningDateId` as a struct property (not a global) - legitimate. User confirmed the app compiles and builds for simulator, so compile-check tasks `T3.25` and `T3.33` are now marked `[x]`.
- **Phase 4 verification evidence:** `HasAPIClient`, `injectAPIClientIfNeeded`, `HasAppServices`, `inject(appServices:)`, and `injectAppServicesIfNeeded()` all still exist in `Networking/APIClient.swift` and `Networking/BackendServices.swift` ✅.

